# Complete Djot Document

This document demonstrates a full-featured Djot document with frontmatter
and various elements working together.

## Introduction

[Djot](https://djot.net) is a light markup syntax created by John MacFarlane,
the creator of [Pandoc](https://pandoc.org). It aims to be a better, more
consistent alternative to Markdown.

{.highlight}
> Djot's syntax is designed to be unambiguous, making it easier to parse
> and produce consistent output across different implementations.

## Features Overview

| Category    | Examples                          |
|:------------|:----------------------------------|
| Inline      | _emphasis_, *strong*, `code`      |
| Blocks      | paragraphs, lists, code blocks    |
| Structure   | headings, divs, blockquotes       |
| Special     | math, footnotes, attributes       |

